ative noise injection. By focusing reconstruction resources only on persistent, high-survivability features, DSE-FGRS achieves superior accuracy-sparse trade-offs compared to static or open-loop approaches. It is particularly effective in large language models and vision transformers, where early-layer features may have delayed but critical impacts on final representations. Extensive experiments show consistent gains over FLAP, Wanda, and CPLI across diverse architectures and tasks, establishing a new paradigm in intelligent, feedback-driven model compression.",
